  "text": "Binding assays on histological sections. Ovaries were collected and were coated with cryoprotectant embedding medium (Tissue-Tek, Miles, Elkhart, IN), frozen in cold isopentane, and then stored at Ϫ20°C. The binding of 125 I-labeled hCG to ovarian frozen sections was studied by an autoradiographic method, as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, ovaries were serially sectioned at a thickness of 5 m with a cryostat. After fixation for 10 min at 4°C in picric acidformaldehyde, sections were stored at Ϫ20°C and then circled with Depex (Gurr, BDH, Poole, UK). hCG was iodinated by the Iodogen method (Sigma, St. Quentin, France) and purified by Sephadex G-50 chromatography. Sections were incubated in a drop of PBS (0.1% BSA, pH 7.4) containing 125 I-labeled hCG (4 ϫ 10 5 cpm/50 l). To determine nonspecific binding, for the tested ligand, an adjacent serial section of ovary was incubated with an excess of unlabeled ligand (500 ng/50 l hCG). At the end of the incubation period, the sections were washed two times in PBS, postfixed in 3% glutaraldehyde-PBS, washed in PBS, air-dried, and stained with Feulgen. For autoradiography, they were then dipped in Kodak NTB-2 emulsion diluted 1:1 with distilled water, air-dried, exposed for 2 wk at 4°C, then developed and fixed by classical procedures.",
